2011-09-14T04:05:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/lupin-gets-u-s-approval-for-drug-to-treat-epilepsy-correct-.html
(Corrects FDA approval status in headline, first
paragraph.)  Lupin Ltd. (LPC) , an Indian drugmaker,
received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration for
its levetiracetam drug to treat epilepsy, according to a
statement on the FDA website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
